<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>When should I start Valentine's Day preparations for my online store?</h3>
<p>Ideally, begin 4-5 weeks before February 14. Stock inventory by mid-January, launch marketing campaigns in late January, and have your fulfillment partner briefed by early February. Use our <a href="/en/calculator/" style="color:#e63329;font-weight:500">pricing calculator</a> to estimate seasonal fulfillment costs.</p>

<h3>What are the best-selling Valentine's Day products online?</h3>
<p>Jewelry, chocolates and sweets, perfume, skincare sets, flowers, personalized gifts, lingerie, and experience vouchers consistently top the charts.</p>

<h3>How important is gift packaging for Valentine's Day orders?</h3>
<p>Extremely important. Over 80% of Valentine's Day purchases are gifts. Offering premium packaging, gift wrapping, and personal message cards significantly increases conversion rates and average order value.</p>

